text:
Hi fiat thanks for leaving me high and dry after spending nearly £30,000 on a brand new fiat 500 that burst into flames after 7 months 

Won't help me out with a car to support a loyal customer 

Disgusting customer service

Fix It Again Tomorrow,   Having spent 10K on a fiat 500 for my Daughter’s first car I tried to reassure her that the acronym maybe related to older models,  17k on the clock,  7 days out of warranty and a £600 repair bill for Master Clutch Cylinder,  Second daughter starts driving in the next few months,  guess where we ARE NOT GOING…….
I absolutely love my fiat 500 and hope to get an electric one next. I think it would be great in pale lemon. So if you are ever wanting to give one to a deserving forever home look no further 😉

Love my Fiat 500 electric La Prima, but after only 2.5 months and a 1000 miles it’s back in the workshop since last Tuesday with errors that the garage can’t seem resolve. Now they can’t even seem to get it to charge ! So they offered me an Enterprise hire car (£28 per day apparently petrol with I believe a £1000 excess down to me which I am not prepared to accept, why should I when Fiat is responsible for my car being off the road ?). After trying since Friday afternoon to try and have a discussion with Fiat Customer Services they finally after multiple phone calls apparently allocated me a case manager, whom I was put through to on my sixth phone call today. I offered two solutions either I use my wife’s car and they pay me a daily compensation rate equivalent to the hire car cost or pay Enterprise their excess waiver fee. Totally unable to negotiate due to “policies” And unable to refer to a higher authority for consideration. My conclusion dealer who sold me the car and the workshop where it is in for repair great ✅✅✅ Fiat Customer Services useless ! PS a quick internet search suggests many people seem to be experiencing error messages with their Fiat 500 electrics, but not as drastic as mine !

I got to experience the new 500e as a courtesy car for a couple of days and all I can say is, if you like small cars this one hits the spot. It’s small, super quiet (obs been electric), very nippy, super easy to drive and great on miles and power. It’s got so many automatic settings you pretty much just need to steer and enjoy. Lane assist, speed limit shown on dash. I also loved the leather interior and sunroof. Highly recommend taking one out for a test drive xx
Hi I have just picked up a 500 Launch edition the steering wheel says techno leather can you tell me what this is please, is it real leather?

Can I ask about customer service please?
I’ve e-mailed and seem to be not getting anywhere! 
I have a fiat 124 spider that you as a company have sent out bulletins over a manufacturing fault in the roof. Yet  my car was never repaired during its warranty period even though it has been to fiat for all its services . I have only just purchased this car second hand 6 weeks ago and the last fiat service was done less than  a 1000miles ago . The fault now means my roof is ruined and you are not willing to help as it now isn’t in fiat warranty. Worries me as to how you are expecting customers to be aware of the fault and then tell you whilst in warranty rather than fixing it when you have the opportunity to look At the car and check! Not good customer service . Hate to imagine what it would be like with an electric car if anything tech went wrong out of warranty that could or should have been fixed!

A lovely car I am sure......but 11 weeks after my daughters fiat 500 went into Stoneacre, Spondon to have an ECU replaced, it is still there. Due to the 'chip' shortage Fiat have provided several dates for delivery of said part which have all come and gone. I have even tried emailing your CEO who did not even have the courtesy to acknowledge the email. No one yet has been able to explain why the ECU has gone, the car is 2015 plate with 16,000 miles on the clock - serviced and maintained......this is my daughters second Fiat 500, however, I fear it will be her last.....
Just ordered one and can't wait for it to arrive!
The only thing fiats where ever best at was being shite and made of cheese
Sad your not making the Fiat 500 in an automatic anymore apart from electric 😢

I have a fiat 500 lounge dual logic, 2018 and 7,000.00 miles on the clock. Warranty ran out july 12th this year. 

Last thur it wouldn't change gear. It is now at my local fiat dealer who are telling me it is the selspeed selector, cost with labour £2000.00. I am waiting to hear if fiat will as a goodwill gesture honour the warranty or at least meet me half way.

Anyone else had this gearbox fault or had experience with fiat uk honouring warranties etc

Bought a new 500c and 500 for my daughter from fiat Milton Keynes - Horrifying to drive away and see DOUBLE THE MILEAGE when car was collected! Totally incompetent management, 2 months later and still to receive £300 compensation on a £8k car. They appear to care, but either completely incompetent or SECOND HAND CAR CROOKS. But I would like to highlight the superb efforts Ellie (Sales Executive) went to to find the right car for my daughter, she was excellent. She was however let down by others in your business who wrongly listed the features on cars in stock and stated a 7400 mileage, when the car we clicked and collected had 13500! Thankfully Ellie unlike her sales Manager in Milton Keynes was professional enough to agree to resolve this very significant mistake that reflected so badly on Glyn Hopkin. Sadly the Glynn Hopkins Fiat were not honourable enough to fulfil the agreement... Still having to fight to get what was promised over two months later... AVOID THIS BRANCH

All well and good, but has quite a few flaws, my Fiat 500 EV with 2000 miles has been in the garage under repair for 7 of the 13 weeks I have had the car, so if you want a car that is in a garage more than with you then go for it, feel free to PM me and I can show you photos of the faults -4 degrees when 28 degree, speed signs read wrong, audio faults and the old classic lane assist that turns you into on coming traffic. Even though I have videos and photos of these faults FIAT UK refuses to believe them and has insisted they drive the car until they show up, so far ice on the road, audio fault and speeds signs have shown fault. Not what I would expect from a new car that I have not seen since July

text:
Dear FIAT,
I thought you may be interested to know that in the Museum of North Bali, Indonesia, there is a FIAT car, unique in that it was the car chosen by the first ever Balinese Governor on Independence. It was purchased new, but as you can see from the photographs enclosed, it is rusting badly. The high humidity is not kind on car bodywork.
The Museum does not have the funds to restore the car, and as the Museum’s main income is from visitor entry fee, there is no hope they can single out this artifact for renovation. As this car is unique and comes with some interesting FIAT history, I was wondering if FIAT could help the Museum restore the car to its former glory, or at least try to arrest further corrosion.

With best regards,

Charles Borman

There are currently 26,805 physical charging locations, (only 8,365 petrol forecourts in the UK – Source: Statista) providing 45,737 electric vehicle charging points across the UK. This represents a 40% increase in the total number of charging devices since July 2022. (Source: Zap Map)

There are approximately 2,000 additional charging points being added every month in the UK (Source: Zap Map)

The vast majority of EV charging is undertaken at home/on domestic off-peak tariffs (typically overnight) which can be as low as 12p/ kWh (Source: Octopus Energy) – it’s no different to plugging in your smartphone each night.

The average car journey in Britain is less than 10 miles and lasts less than 25 minutes (National Travel Survey Statistics – UK Government Department of Transport website)

EV’s are 60 times LESS likely to catch fire than their ICE counterparts (25.1 incidences per 100,000 sales compared with 1,529.9 incidences per 100,000 sales) – Source: Inside EVs

text:
Hmm, nice-ish car, but it rather suffers from being neither one thing nor the other. It's not a proper convertible given the roof rails stay in position and the hood when folded takes up the space the rear window would. And when the hoods up it has no tailgate, losing the flexibility of the hatchback. 

Being practical, to me it would have been better to have the standard hatchback with a full length sliding sunroof. This would have given nearly as much open roof as the convertible, left the rear window unobstructed and preserved the hatchback versatility.

text:
Mal ehrlich 👋🤣 es ist doch schon lange offiziell bekannt und zu überprüfen..... 1)  Um eine Batterie eines E-Autos herzustellen wird so viel Gift und Energie gebraucht um ein Benziner mit 200.000 km zu fahren 2) um einen Windrädchen aufzustellen müssen Unmengen von Wälder abgeholzt werden die unsere Luft eigentlich reinigen 3 ) es wird so viel Beton in das Fundament gepumpt ,das Straßen dorthin gebaut werden um diese extreme Last der Lkws zu tragen 4) die Windrädchen werden alle 20 Jahre ausgewechselt wenn Sie bis dorthin überhaupt noch funktionieren 5) die Rotorblätter sind aus speziellem Material das bis heute noch nicht entsorgt werden kann ( meist werden sie im Boden einfach vergraben ) 6) Unser Stromnetz ist bekanntlich nicht ausgelegt für Elektroautos und Wärmepumpen Heizungen für jeden Bürger ( und wir nutzen zur Zeit nicht einmal 5% von 100% benötigter Energie ) .....7) bei noch mehr Stromverbrauch von Elektroautos und Wärmepumpen bricht das Stromnetz in den Städten zusammen ( die Stromleitungen im Boden verglühen da sie die Wärme nicht abgeben können ! ) ......8) Mit kohlekraft , dreckigen Gas aus Amerika , überteuerte Rohstoff von allen Ländern geht die Umwelt bestimmt noch schneller kaputt? 
9) in Deutschland gibt es von zwei, nur noch eine Firma die Batterien von Autos entsorgen kann 🫣 wie viel Gift durch jeder einzelne Batterie dann noch in die Umwelt gepumpt wird ....ist überhaupt noch nicht bekannt ! 
PS... Ich habe noch nie die AFD gewählt und die Nazi Keule könnt ihr sehr gerne an euch selbst anwenden um euch zu hinterfragen 👋😜 ob es dann noch was nützt könnt ihr euren Kindern erzählen, wenn sie dann eure Schuld vielleicht noch überleben ...... Liebe Grüße und Gottes unendlichen Segen wünsche ich meinen Freunden und meinen Feinden von ganzem Herzen denn ihr könnt es wirklich brauchen 🥰🙌💞
